___NOTES___

Created on 12/31/2024
PixelFly Server-Side Event Tracking Template
Version 1.0.5

This template sends events to PixelFly's server-side tracking endpoint,
which then forwards to Meta CAPI, GA4 Measurement Protocol, and other platforms.

Changes in 1.0.5:
- Fixed: send_pixel permission now allows any URL for custom domain support
- Users can now use custom tracking domains (e.g., pixels.yourdomain.com)

Changes in 1.0.4:
- Added: Tax, Shipping, and Coupon Code fields in Event Data section
- These fields are sent to both Meta CAPI and GA4 for purchase events

Changes in 1.0.3:
- Added: Client ID and Session ID variable fields in Advanced Options
- These allow session tracking when used with GTM variables

Changes in 1.0.2:
- Fixed: GTM internal events (gtm.js, gtm.dom, gtm.load, etc.) are now filtered out
- These events were being sent unnecessarily and cluttering analytics

Changes in 1.0.1:
- Fixed permission errors for inject_script and access_globals
- Switched to sendPixel with GET request approach
- Added proper URL patterns for send_pixel permission

For support, visit: https://pixelfly.io/docs

